In order to test QwAnalysis_MySQL, 
how to configure "localhost" MySQL server.


* install MySQL server

* start the sevice by
  [] /etc/init.d/mysqld start


* create databases

  [] mysql -u root -p mysql

  mysql> show databases;
  +--------------------+
  | Database           |
  +--------------------+
  | information_schema | 
  | mysql              | 
  +--------------------+
  
  mysql> create database qw_test;
  mysql> show databases;
  +--------------------+
  | Database           |
  +--------------------+
  | information_schema | 
  | mysql              | 
  | qw_test            | 
  +--------------------+
  

* create a test qweak user

  [] mysql -u root -p mysql

   mysql> create user qwreplay@localhost identified by 'password';

   mysql> select host, user from mysql.user;
   +-----------+------------------+
   | host      | user             |
   +-----------+------------------+
   | localhost | debian-sys-maint | 
   | localhost | qwreplay         | 
   | localhost | root             | 
   +-----------+------------------+

   mysql> grant select, insert, update, execute on `qw\_%`.* to qwreplay@localhost;

   mysql> show grants for qwreplay@localhost;
   +---------------------------------------------------------------------
   | Grants for qwreplay@localhost                                       
   +---------------------------------------------------------------------
   | GRANT USAGE ON *.* TO 'qwreplay'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY PASSWORD 
   | GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, EXECUTE ON `qw\_%`.* TO 'qwreplay'@'localhost'
   +---------------------------------------------------------------------

   mysql> select host, user from mysql.user;
   +-----------+------------------+
   | host      | user             |
   +-----------+------------------+
   | localhost | debian-sys-maint | 
   | localhost | qwreplay         | 
   | localhost | root             | 
   +-----------+------------------+

* setup qw_test databases by using qw_test.sql file

  [] mysql -u root -p  qw_test < qw_test.sql


* run 

  One example,

  [] qwanalysis_mysql -r 753 -e 0:1

..........................

 QwDatabase MySQL  v5.0.51a-24+lenny3  -----------------
 Database server :  localhost name   :      qw_test user   : qwreplay port   :      0
